- Central 9P-like protocol, notp

With each *remote* transaction:
```
struct notp_ksig
{
    uint16_t protocol;
    int8_t sig[];
};

struct notp_msg
{
    notp_sig sig;   /* Cryptographic signature of the following data, signed
                       by the kernel */
    int8_t cmd;     /* Single-character command, e.g. "R" for read */
    uint32_t fd;    /* File descriptor */
    uint64_t nonce; /* Aribitrary value, current time works best */

    optional
        struct
        {
            uint32_t size;  /* Size of the following data */
            int8_t data[];
        } 
};
```

Local transactions simply lack the kernel signature.
